place.name: SOUTH WARNBOROUGH
place.gazetteerText: WARNBOROUGH (South), a parish in Hartley-Wintney district, Hants; 6 miles S W of Winchfield r. station. It has a post-office under Winchfield. Acres, 2,569. Real property, £3,125. Pop., 369. Houses, 75. W. Park is the seat of T. Wayne, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Winchester. Value, £594.* Patron, St. John's College, Oxford. Charities, £13. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
